snippet.textDisplay: The original 'Bhatiali' tune of the song (which is sung in northern part of Bangladesh and West Bengal) fitted well in Saurav Moni's voice and Shaan made it euphonious for listeners of other languages. It's a great effort of them to popularise a folk Bangla song to more listeners. Heartfelt thanks and gratitude from Bangladesh!!

snippet.textDisplay: Since 'Bhatiyali' is a slow folk song, it was supposed to be blended with a find malt of music. Suddenly, after 7th minute the tempo of the song increased rapidly which cause some damage to the flavour of 'Bhatiyali'. It could have been done with an uniform acceleration. The acting of Shantanu Mujkherjee is very good. Let him be a hero. This kind of music is like scotch whiskey which intoxicates slowly but steadily. Please have some idea from Raheman about blending of music. Overall a nice approach.. hope to listen a better music in future.. thanks
